oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Andrews family coat of arms, 1917
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: B. F. Johnson, Incorporated
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description:
Painting of the Andrews family coat of arms. The crest features a greyhound's head atop a knight's helmet above a shield. The Andrews family motto below the sheild, "Victrix Fortunae Sapientia," translates as "Wisdom is the conqueror of fortune." The caption on the reverse side of the painted image reads "This coat of arms was painted in the Heraldic Department of B. F. Johnson, INC. Biography-Family History, Genealogy-Heraldry. 926 Pennsylvania Avenue, Northwest Washington D. C., U. S. A."
This item is undated but is believed to have been created at the same time as the document entitled "Ye Armes of Ye Anciente Familie of Andrews," in 1917.
